{"key":"post-9837629","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9837629</id>\n<content>Then go ahead and repeat the same mistakes that have been made thousands of times before you.&amp;nbsp; Every new grower experiments with plants or at least thinks of it.&amp;nbsp; However, the fact remains that plants and semi-sterile growing techniques for indoor mushrooms are mutually exclusive.&amp;nbsp; It would take a room full of plants to absorb the CO2 from one terrarium, and even if it did, it wouldn't help much.&amp;nbsp; FRESH AIR is what is required for good fruiting and performance, not oxygen.&amp;nbsp; We've also had many growers including myself pump pure O2 from tanks and liquid oxygen directly into their terrariums with zero benefit.&amp;nbsp; If you want to experiment, then go ahead and do it, but don't call others asses for trying to point you in the right direction.&amp;nbsp; If you were trying to develop a square wheel for cars, you'd get the same advice.&amp;nbsp; All you need to do is drill some holes in your terrarium, and you'll have all the fresh air you need.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9837826</next>\n<prev>9837592</prev>\n<first>9834922</first>\n<last>9843013</last>\n<when>1235233167</when>\n<utime>02/21/09 06:19 PM</utime>\n</post>"}